Quel est la variation du Ca entre 2 mois en 2025

Requête SQL envoyée :

SELECT
    rcm.year AS year,
    rcm.month AS month,
    rcm.ca_ht AS chiffre_affaire,
    LAG(rcm.ca_ht, 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY rcm.year, rcm.month) AS previous_month_ca,
    rcm.ca_ht - LAG(rcm.ca_ht, 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY rcm.year, rcm.month) AS ca_variation
FROM
    reporting_ca_monthly rcm
WHERE
    rcm.year = 2025
ORDER BY
    rcm.year,
    rcm.month;

Requête SQL envoyée :

SELECT
    rcm.year AS year,
    rcm.month AS month,
    rcm.ca_ht AS chiffre_affaire,
    LAG(rcm.ca_ht, 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY rcm.year, rcm.month) AS previous_month_ca,
    rcm.ca_ht - LAG(rcm.ca_ht, 1, 0) OVER (ORDER BY rcm.year, rcm.month) AS ca_variation
FROM
    reporting_ca_monthly rcm
WHERE
    rcm.year = 2025
GROUP BY
   rcm.year, rcm.month
ORDER BY
    rcm.year,
    rcm.month;

SELECT
    dp.year AS year,
    dp.month AS month,
    COUNT(DISTINCT dp.MSISDN) AS active_4g_park
FROM
    daily_parc_data_4g dp
JOIN
    monthly_clients mc ON dp.MSISDN = mc.MSISDN AND dp.year = mc.year AND dp.month = mc.month
WHERE
    dp.year = 2025
    AND dp.month = 4
    AND mc.compatible_network = '4G'
GROUP BY
    dp.year,
    dp.month
ORDER BY
    dp.year,
    dp.month;
